Social Good through Public Finance and Wealth Management
Friday, March 12th
12-1pm ET
Register via Handshake

Join us for a candid conversation with MSPPM alums Jenai Booker and Shawneil Campbell, from the class of 2015. In this conversation they aim to do three things: (1) Demystify preconceived notions about the fields of Public Finance and Wealth Management; (2) Illustrate how to get the most out of your MSPPM degree; and (3) Network with all of you. We look forward to a fruitful conversation.

node.text:
Two Carnegie Mellon alumni, including a #cmuece grad, contributed to ensuring a smooth Inauguration Day. General Bowie (ECE 1989) was the first to salute President Joe Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris. 

For Bowie, a West Baltimore native and 1989 graduate of CMU’s College of Engineering, January 20, 2021, was his fourth time playing a leadership role in a presidential inauguration. This year, as Deputy Commanding General — Inauguration, Bowie was tasked with organizing all the military logistics of the ceremony on that day.

#cmualumni

accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Carnegie Mellon ECE on March 31, 2021 tagging @carnegiemellon, @cmuengineering, @cmu_dietrichhss, and @cmu_bme. May be an image of 1 person, standing, tree and outdoors.

node.text:
Esther Bedoyan, a junior majoring ECE and biomedical engineering with a minor in Chinese studies, has received the prestigious 2021 Barry Goldwater Scholarship to encourage her pursuit of a research career.

Since the fall of 2020, Bedoyan has been conducting research in Dr. Maysam Chamanzar’s lab focusing on developing an adaptive frequency domain filtering technique that removes electrical interference from electrophysiology data.

“I’ve had a lot of fun with this project. I’ve been able to independently develop this filtering technique and test its performance on real electrophysiology recordings collected from neural organoids and present my findings at multiple conferences and poster presentations,” Bedoyan said.

Upon graduation, she plans on completing the Integrated Masters Bachelor Program at CMU, then pursuing a Ph.D.

#goldwaterscholarship #engineer #cmuece @carnegiemellon @cmuengineering

node.text:
In a recent Nature Communications Biology paper, #cmuece PhD student Alireza Chamanzar demonstrates an algorithm called #SilenceMap to locate regions of neural silence using an EEG, a widely accessible device that measures brain activity. 

A region of silence in the brain can be a sign of stroke or a brain tumor. These silences can also result from brain damage or tissue death. Locating the regions of neural silence could ensure patients are diagnosed earlier and allow their treatment to begin sooner.

#brainresearch
